docs.title: AFNI
docs.description: AFNI (Analysis of Functional NeuroImages) is a leading software suite of C, Python, R programs and shell scripts primarily developed for the analysis and display of multiple MRI modalities: anatomical, functional MRI (FMRI) and diffusion weighted (DW) data. It is freely available (both as open source code and as precompiled binaries) for research purposes. The software is made to run on virtually any Unix system with X11 and Motif displays. Binary packages are provided for MacOS and Linux systems such as Fedora, CentOS/Red Hat and Ubuntu (which includes the Windows Subsystem for Linux).
Prints out sort-of-useful information from a 3D dataset's header

docs.title: Aform Real Matrix
docs.description: Display full 3x4 'aform_real' matrix (AFNI's RAI equivalent of the sform matrix in NIFTI, may contain obliquity info), with comment line first

docs.title: Aform Real Matrix (One Line)
docs.description: Display full 'aform_real' matrix (see '-aform_real') as 1 row of 12 numbers. No additional comment

docs.title: Aform Real Matrix (Refit Orientation)
docs.description: Display full 3x4 'aform_real' matrix (see '-aform_real') *if* the dset were reoriented (via 3drefit) to new orient XXX. Includes comment line first

docs.title: Is Aform Real Orthogonal
docs.description: If true, aform_real == aform_orth, which should be a very common occurrence

docs.title: Aform Orthogonal Matrix
docs.description: Display full 3x4 'aform_orth' matrix (AFNI's RAI matrix equivalent of the NIFTI quaternion, which may contain obliquity info), with comment line first. This matrix is the orthogonalized form of aform_real, and very often AFNI-produced dsets, we will have: aform_orth == aform_real

docs.title: Permutation to Orientation
docs.description: Display 3x3 permutation matrix to go from the dset's current orientation to the YYY orient

docs.title: Same Grid
docs.description: Output 1 if the grid is identical between two dsets, 0 otherwise. For -same_grid to be 1, all of -same_dim, -same_delta, -same_orient, -same_center, and -same_obl must return 1

docs.title: Same Dimensions
docs.description: 1 if dimensions (nx, ny, nz) are the same between dset pairs

docs.title: Same Voxel Sizes
docs.description: 1 if voxel sizes are the same between dset pairs

docs.title: Same Orientation
docs.description: 1 if orientation is the same between dset pairs

docs.title: Same Geometric Center
docs.description: 1 if geometric center is the same between dset pairs

docs.title: Same Obliquity
docs.description: 1 if obliquity is the same between dset pairs

docs.title: Same All Grid
docs.description: Equivalent to listing all of -same_dim, -same_delta, -same_orient, -same_center, and -same_obl on the command line

docs.title: Value Difference
docs.description: Output the sum of absolute differences of all voxels in the dataset pair. A -1.0 value indicates a grid mismatch between volume pairs

docs.title: Scaled Value Difference
docs.description: Same as -val_diff, but the sum is divided (scaled) by the total number of voxels that are not zero in at least one of the two datasets

docs.title: Monogamous Pairs
docs.description: Instead of pairing each dset with the first, pair each couple separately. This requires you to have an even number of dsets on the command line
